----------------------------------------------------------
README
----------------------------------------------------------


This folder contains several examples of how to compute noise sensitivity kernels 
for global and regional simulations
(various resolutions: global 600 CPUs/ regional 400 CPUs)


--------------


Example: To run a global noise simulation, type for example:

./run_this_example.sh global_long

this will setup all scripts and tools in sub-directory global_long/. 
it can then be used as a run directory with e.g. the PBS job-script "job_NOISE123_pbs.submit_atten.sh".

Please modify these scripts according to your specifics.



---------------



For more details, please see these routines being described and used in article:

Tromp, J., Y. Luo, S. Hanasoge and D. Peter, 2010. 
Noise Cross-Correlation Sensitivity Kernels, 
Geophys. J. Int., 183 (2), 791-819.

